  "texts": [
    "By definition of the weak * topology (the fact that it is locally convex suffices) there exists a convex open set V n ⊂ U n with ρ ∈ V n. Let us take A = V n and apply Proposition 4.2 obtaining thereby u n ∈ Y such thatu n (ρ n) > sup x∈B X |u n (T (x))|.",
    "(4.2)Since the right hand side is larger than or equal to 0, we in particular have u n (ρ n) > 0.",
    "Letv n = 1 nu n (ρ n) u n ∈ Y.Then we have∥v n ∥ Y ≥ |v n (nρ n)| = 1 nu n (ρ n) u n (nρ n) = 1,by definition of v n, using also the fact that ∥nρ n ∥ Y * ≤ 1.",
    "This asserts item (i).",
    "For item (ii), we have supx∈B X |⟨T (x), v n ⟩| = sup x∈B X |⟨T (x), 1 nu n (ρ n) u n ⟩| < 1 nu n (ρ n) u n (ρ n) = 1 n,where in the last inequality we used (4.2).Remark 4.5."
